    "body": "Hey @louvivien, \n\nYou can see the minimum suggested requirements for a Besu network here: https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/latest/HowTo/Get-Started/System-Requirements/\n\nIf you are trying to run a named network (i.e. Mainnet, Ropsten, etc.) you will need 8GB of RAM for the JVM. I'm not sure if that is within the scope of the AWS free tier. Note that if you want to test on a smaller instance, you will be good to run a Besu private network using 4GB of RAM. \n\nI'll close this for now, but please re-open if you have any additional questions! ",
